   <summary>About the commit history</summary>
   <p>The original commits from the main repository are not preserved when code is copied to this repository because they contain references to files that don't exist in this repository. So, the Cardinal CI bot will create new commits that contain changes for only the files that are published to the self-hosted repository.</p>
   <p>Unfortuntely, I am but a mere git mortal so this process results in losing the original commit messages. The commits in this repository are also less granular, with each commit each containing everything from the last merge to main upstream.</p>
-  <p>I recognize the issues that this will create for prospective contributors. I've included a copy of the CI job that publishes this code at <code>publish-oss.yaml</code> in case anyone wants to improve on it.</p>
+  <p>I recognize the issues that this will create for prospective contributors. If people actually want to use this repo then I'll improve it.</p>
 </details>
 
